  "text": "The Apache Kafka repository contains consumer group partition assignment strategy implementations across two main locations:\n\n**Consumer Client Implementations (clients module):**\nThe primary partition assignment strategies are implemented in the clients module under org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer. The base class AbstractPartitionAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractPartitionAssignor.java) implements the ConsumerPartitionAssignor interface and serves as the foundation for all consumer-side partition assignors.\n\nThe four main assignor implementations extend either AbstractPartitionAssignor directly or through AbstractStickyAssignor:\n\n1. RangeAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RangeAssignor.java) - Assigns consecutive partitions to each consumer, the default strategy.\n\n2. RoundRobinAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RoundRobinAssignor.java) - Distributes partitions in round-robin fashion across consumers.\n\n3. StickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/StickyAssignor.java) - Minimizes partition movements during rebalancing while maintaining reasonably balanced assignments. It extends AbstractStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractStickyAssignor.java).\n\n4. CooperativeStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/CooperativeStickyAssignor.java) - A cooperative rebalancing variant of StickyAssignor that also extends AbstractStickyAssignor, allowing only reassigned partitions to be revoked.\n\n**Group Coordinator Implementation:**\nAdditionally, there is a separate RangeAssignor implementation in the group-coordinator module (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/assignor/RangeAssignor.java) that implements ConsumerGroupPartitionAssignor, which is used by the newer group coordinator protocol.\n\n**Inheritance Hierarchy:**\n- AbstractPartitionAssignor (base class for consumer client assignors)\n  - RangeAssignor (direct child)\n  - RoundRobinAssignor (direct child)\n  - AbstractStickyAssignor (intermediate base class)\n    - StickyAssignor\n    - CooperativeStickyAssignor"
}

